[1mCompetition

How would you like to win a copy of Acid Software's brilliant Amiga
programming language, Blitz Basic 2.1? I'm sure you'd love that
wouldn't you? Well, we're going to go one better and offer you the
chance of winning Ultimate Blitz Basic 2.1 on CD!

All you have to do is this:

   1) Answer the question below
   2) If you live outside the UK, write some instructions on how
      to send thngs to your country. (Optional)
   3) Send off your entry with the answer on it to:

      Trogladite Software
      World Of Amiga Compo
      81 Doncaster Road
      Selby
      North Yorkshire
      YO8 9BU
      ENGLAND

And here's the question you need to answer to stand a chance of winning:

   Q. What does the term MIPS stand for?
      (a) Millions of Instructions Per Second
      (b) Micro Instruction Pixel Speed
      (c) Millionth Instruction Personal Security

Send your answers to the address above, and you could win the wonderful
Ultimate Blitz CD

Ultimate Blitz CD System Requirements:
   CD-Drive
   Any Processor
   1MB RAM
   Some Hard Disk Space

Entries must be received by 13th April. Any entries which are recieved
after this date will be thrown in the bin. Sorry. Strict deadlines to
stick to you see.

